      "message": "PTAL (when you have the chance, for obvious reasons). I\u0027ve cleared previous +1\u0027s since this has diverged a lot from the initial patchset, based on discussions in the Recipe Engine Development chat.\n\nI think this can serve as a reasonable basis for writing python-free recipes in Go. Broad reviewer list to let various interested parties peek at the APIs, please add others who you know may be interested.\n\nNote that this only covers concurrency-safe manipulation of the Build message, including logging streams. This is intentionally light (even though the implementation looks a bit exciting).\n\nFor a full \"recipes\" effort, I think we\u0027ll also want to lay down some conventions about how modules should be initialized from properties, how modules should implement fakes, etc. I have some ideas, but I think this will provide value in the meantime.",
